From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 10:25:38 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] dcomp: Implement IDCompositionDesktopDevice with DXVK back buffer interop.

Wine's dcomp.dll previously stubbed every COM entry point with
E_NOTIMPL, which made CEF (Chromium Embedded Framework, used by
Battle.net and other Electron-style apps) either fall back to GDI
rendering or refuse to draw at all.

Implement the COM surface required for CEF's compositor path:
IDCompositionDesktopDevice, IDCompositionVisual2, IDCompositionSurface,
and IDCompositionTarget.  Each Commit() snapshots the bound DXVK
swap chain's current back buffer through IDXGIVkInteropSurface and
forwards it to the windowing driver via WM_WAYLAND_COMPOSE_ATTACH,
on a ~60 Hz internal ticker so we present at compositor cadence
without busy-spinning.

This is the hardware-accelerated half of the CEF-on-Wayland pipeline;
the corresponding driver-side bridge is added in a follow-up patch.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
